Iavan Pijoos, News24(File) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; A security guard was shot and wounded in a shopping centre in End Street, central Johannesburg, on Thursday evening, paramedics said.The man had been shot in the stomach and was in a serious condition, ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said.Paramedics found him in the back of a shop, in a storeroom.An unknown number of gunmen apparently entered the shop and the guard was shot while trying to stop them, Meiring said.He was transported to a private hospital in Johannesburg.Police were not immediately available for comment.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.